To simplify \(-\tfrac{69}{120}\), factor out the greatest common divisor of 69 and 120, which is 3:

\[
-\frac{69}{120}
= -\frac{3\cdot 23}{3\cdot 40}
= -\frac{23}{40}.
\]

To simplify \(-\tfrac{120}{192}\), note that \(\gcd(120,192)=24\). Dividing numerator and denominator by 24 gives

\[
-\frac{120}{192}
= -\frac{120÷24}{192÷24}
= -\frac{5}{8}.
\]

First multiply numerators and denominators, then simplify:

\[
-\frac{10}{28}\cdot\frac{8}{15}
=\frac{-10\cdot 8}{28\cdot 15}
