=\frac{-4}{21}.
\]

So the product is \(-4/21\).

To divide, multiply by the reciprocal of the second fraction:

\[
- \tfrac{3}{5} \div \tfrac{p}{7}
= -\tfrac{3}{5}\times \tfrac{7}{p}
= -\tfrac{3\cdot 7}{5\cdot p}
= -\tfrac{21}{5p},
\]

where \(p\neq0\).

To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
\frac{\frac{3}{7}}{\frac{6}{11}}
= \frac{3}{7}\times \frac{11}{6}
= \frac{3\cdot 11}{7\cdot 6}
= \frac{33}{42}
= \frac{11}{14}.
\]

To simplify \(\frac{\frac{a}{8}}{\frac{ab}{6}}\), rewrite as a multiplication by the reciprocal:

\[
\frac{a/8}{\,ab/6\,}
= \frac{a}{8}\;\times\;\frac{6}{ab}
= \frac{6a}{8ab}
= \frac{6}{8b}
= \frac{3}{4b}.
\]

Hence the expression simplifies to \(\displaystyle \frac{3}{4b}\), assuming \(a\neq0\) and \(b\neq0\).

To simplify \(\displaystyle \frac{\tfrac p2}{\tfrac{p q}{8}}\), rewrite the division as multiplication by the reciprocal:

\[
\frac{p/2}{(p q)/8}
= \frac{p}{2}\;\times\;\frac{8}{p q}
= \frac{8p}{2\,p\,q}
= \frac{8}{2q}
= \frac{4}{q},
\]

provided \(p\neq0\) and \(q\neq0\).
